pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `addresses` ( `ID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `CITY` varchar(50) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `ADDRESS` varchar(100) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `PSC` mediumint(8) unsigned NOT NULL, `LAT` float NOT NULL, `LON` float NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=784 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_slovak_ci;

CREATE TABLE `schools` ( `ID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `NAME` varchar(200) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `ADDRESS_ID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`), KEY `ADDRESS_ID` (`ADDRESS_ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=784 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_slovak_ci;

CREATE TABLE `users` ( `ID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `FIRSTNAME` varchar(50) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `SURNAME` varchar(50) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `EMAIL` varchar(254) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, `SCHOOL_ID` int(10) unsigned DEFAULT NULL, `ADDRESS_ID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL, `PASSWORD` varchar(64) COLLATE utf8_slovak_ci NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`), UNIQUE KEY `EMAIL` (`EMAIL`), KEY `SCHOOL_ID` (`SCHOOL_ID`), KEY `SCHOOL_ID_2` (`SCHOOL_ID`), KEY `ADDRESS_ID` (`ADDRESS_ID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_slovak_ci;
